      "description": "Matrix multiplication is a method whereby two matrices are multiplied to produce another matrix.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 200
    },
    {
      "id": "text_1",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "The number of columns in the first matrix must match the number of rows in the second matrix for them to be compatible for multiplication.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 260
    },
    {
      "id": "text_2",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "To multiply, take the dot product between rows of the first matrix and columns of the second matrix.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 320
    },
    {
      "id": "text_3",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Resulting matrices represent transformations such as rotations or scaling within vector spaces.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 380
    },
    {
      "id": "text_4",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Matrix multiplication is associative but not commutative.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 440
    }
